Title: THE SIEGE OF CHARLESTON.
Abstract: The United States steam transport Arago HENRY A. GADSDEN, commanding, from Port Royal, S.C., at 10:30 A.M., and Charleston Bar at 5 P.M., on Thursday, July 23, arrived at this port yesterday afternoon, bringing 100 first, and 172 second class, passengers, the usual mails, and having the prize steamer Emma in tow.

Title: OPERATIONS AGAINST CHARLESTON
Abstract: The advent of Gen. GILLMORE has awakened this Department from its lethargy. Taking Folly Island as the base, he has commenced siege operations against Charleston which bid fair to result successfully.
